    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-05-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-05-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="465"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Chargé <persName type="to">Brown</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-05-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 13, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of Mr. Combs’s
                    dispatch No. 270, of the 26th ultimo, inclosing a copy of correspondence
                    relating to the complaint of Mr. Al. Stebbins and his wife that a squad of
                    soldiers, by the orders of Meleton Agreda, commandante of La Gomera, forcibly
                    entered his premises on July 30 and 31, 1904, took therefrom certain property,
                    and assaulted Mrs. Stebbins.</p>
                <p>In reply I have to say that Mr. Combs’s efforts to bring about an unofficial
                    adjustment of the matter by the payment to the injured parties of a small sum is
                    approved by the Department.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">F. B. Loomis.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
